278
00:36:06,331 --> 00:36:09,418
We'd never made love so well,
so long.

279
00:36:10,378 --> 00:36:14,423
We learned something.
Me from you. You from me.

280
00:36:15,174 --> 00:36:18,804
When I woke up, you were
still sleeping. Like a child.

281
00:36:19,012 --> 00:36:20,180
I'm older than you.

282
00:36:20,389 --> 00:36:22,391
- One year!
- No, two.

283
00:36:22,599 --> 00:36:27,939
Okay. Two. When I saw you, I got
scared. What is this leading to?

284
00:36:28,856 --> 00:36:30,608
You sound a little down.

285
00:36:31,484 --> 00:36:32,902
Are you nervous
about your exams?

286
00:36:33,111 --> 00:36:36,698
About what I'm going to do.
Will it be enough for you?

287
00:36:36,907 --> 00:36:37,825
Why not go bowling?

288
00:36:38,909 --> 00:36:40,661
I opened all my books.

289
00:36:41,245 --> 00:36:42,831
Maybe.
Do you have a coin?

290
00:36:43,039 --> 00:36:43,873
Yes.

291
00:36:44,082 --> 00:36:48,086
Flip It. Tails is bowling.
Heads is Penal Code.

292
00:36:53,467 --> 00:36:55,094
Tails. Bowling.

293
00:36:55,928 --> 00:36:57,763
I'll work for an hour,
then I'll call you.

294
00:36:57,972 --> 00:36:58,931
Or I will.

295
00:36:59,140 --> 00:37:01,059
I'll wait. If I go out,

296
00:37:01,268 --> 00:37:03,478
It's just to buy cigarettes.

297
00:37:09,986 --> 00:37:11,654
You didn't listen?

298
00:37:15,408 --> 00:37:18,370
What a shame. It was romantic.

299
00:37:19,663 --> 00:37:21,206
I heard the beginning.

300
00:37:22,082 --> 00:37:23,291
They're in love.

301
00:37:25,420 --> 00:37:26,045
Yes.

302
00:37:28,089 --> 00:37:30,758
He hasn't met the right woman yet.

303
00:37:32,176 --> 00:37:33,345
How do you know?

304
00:37:34,388 --> 00:37:36,974
I watch them from my window.

305
00:37:41,521 --> 00:37:42,981
You think I'm a bastard?

306
00:37:43,231 --> 00:37:44,065
Yes.

307
00:37:44,566 --> 00:37:45,734
Come look.

308
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:53,868
He bought a telephone in Japan
that uses another wavelength.

309
00:37:55,703 --> 00:37:59,291
My radio can't pick it up.
Too bad.

310
00:38:01,042 --> 00:38:05,422
I think he's responsible for most
of the heroin trade in Geneva.

311
00:38:06,631 --> 00:38:08,134
We have nothing on him.

312
00:38:09,302 --> 00:38:10,928
He never takes risks.

313
00:38:17,102 --> 00:38:18,353
Do you like him?

314
00:38:18,604 --> 00:38:19,354
Very much.

315
00:38:22,941 --> 00:38:23,860
I'll call him.

316
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:27,363
You have his phone number?

317
00:38:53,768 --> 00:38:54,894
You deserve to die.

318
00:39:13,664 --> 00:39:14,457
What did I do?

319
00:39:16,168 --> 00:39:18,003
Here's his phone number.

320
00:39:18,587 --> 00:39:22,341
If you feel like saying
mean things to him, don't hesitate.

321
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:37,107
At 10 o'clock, I turned off
the lights. I couldn't seep.

322
00:39:37,316 --> 00:39:39,693
Next program.
Not very interesting.

323
00:39:40,028 --> 00:39:43,490
I kept tossing and turning.
It kept hurting.

324
00:39:44,157 --> 00:39:45,992
it still does.

325
00:39:46,952 --> 00:39:48,621
I haven't done the errands.

326
00:39:49,830 --> 00:39:50,998
I'm sorry, mother.

327
00:39:51,207 --> 00:39:52,959
I have no milk or bread.

328
00:39:53,167 --> 00:39:56,462
I bought you some.
I put it in the freezer.

329
00:39:57,506 --> 00:39:58,590
I ate it all.

330
00:39:58,799 --> 00:40:00,884
You didn't eat 7 loaves

331
00:40:01,218 --> 00:40:03,303
in #4##days.
I'm sick##of##this#.

332
00:40:05,848 --> 00:40:07,809
Go do her errands.

333
00:40:09,268 --> 00:40:10,853
Maybe you'd feel better.

334
00:40:17,903 --> 00:40:18,779
Maybe she's the one

335
00:40:18,987 --> 00:40:20,280
who'd feel better.

336
00:40:21,073 --> 00:40:23,243
Why did you pick up Rita?

337
00:40:24,869 --> 00:40:26,579
Because I'd run over her.

338
00:40:27,163 --> 00:40:28,790
She was bleeding.

339
00:40:29,874 --> 00:40:31,627
Otherwise,
you'd have felt guilty.

340
00:40:32,711 --> 00:40:36,382
You'd have dreamt of a dog
with a crushed skull.

341
00:40:38,133 --> 00:40:38,759
Yes.

342
00:40:39,469 --> 00:40:41,429
So who did you do it for?

343
00:40:47,269 --> 00:40:50,106
Don't bother
doing that Lady's errands.

344
00:40:50,314 --> 00:40:51,899
She has everything she needs.

345
00:40:52,525 --> 00:40:54,777
She wants to see her daughter.

346
00:40:56,028 --> 00:40:57,781
She already came 5 times,

347
00:40:57,990 --> 00:41:00,617
when her mother
faked a heart attack.

348
00:41:02,911 --> 00:41:06,708
After she dies,
I'll have to call the daughter.

349
00:41:08,751 --> 00:41:10,336
She doesn't believe her any more.

350
00:41:14,925 --> 00:41:16,135
You're mistaken.

351
00:41:17,344 --> 00:41:18,554
About what?

352
00:41:19,680 --> 00:41:20,764
About everything.

353
00:41:23,435 --> 00:41:24,310
Everything.

354
00:41:30,359 --> 00:41:31,277
People aren't bad.

355
00:41:31,610 --> 00:41:32,778
It's not true.

356
00:41:34,572 --> 00:41:35,364
Yes.

357
00:41:35,906 --> 00:41:37,283
They may be weak sometimes...

358
00:41:38,744 --> 00:41:42,497
The boy who learned
his father wasn't his father...

359
00:41:42,706 --> 00:41:44,666
your boyfriend or your brother?

360
00:41:47,503 --> 00:41:48,463
My brother.

361
00:41:48,671 --> 00:41:50,047
How old is he?

362
00:41:52,508 --> 00:41:53,342
16.

363
00:41:53,551 --> 00:41:56,138
How long
has he been shooting up?

364
00:41:59,057 --> 00:42:00,225
How do you know?

365
00:42:00,475 --> 00:42:02,394
it wasn't hard to guess.

366
00:42:09,235 --> 00:42:11,946
I can only feel pity for you.

367
00:42:20,205 --> 00:42:21,458
Maybe you don't know.

368
00:42:21,833 --> 00:42:23,376
Your dog is pregnant.

369
00:44:44,741 --> 00:44:45,577
It's Valentine.

370
00:44:45,785 --> 00:44:46,995
Hello, darling.

371
00:44:47,203 --> 00:44:48,871
Mom, did Marc come?

372
00:44:49,080 --> 00:44:52,166
Two days ago. With his girlfriend.
Do you know her?

373
00:44:52,375 --> 00:44:53,460
Yes. Marie.

374
00:44:53,669 --> 00:44:56,505
We're all together.
They're watching TV.

375
00:44:57,381 --> 00:44:58,590
I'm sorry
I can't be there.

376
00:44:58,799 --> 00:45:00,926
Too bad.
It's like old times.

377
00:45:01,135 --> 00:45:02,804
Your brother's a good boy.

378
00:45:03,013 --> 00:45:04,180
Can I talk to him?

379
00:45:04,389 --> 00:45:05,932
Marci
He's coming.

380
00:45:06,141 --> 00:45:07,809
Call me, Mom.
I love you.

381
00:45:08,351 --> 00:45:09,019
Hi, Valentine.

382
00:45:09,227 --> 00:45:11,439
Thanks for going there.

383
00:45:11,647 --> 00:45:14,358
We're leaving tomorrow.
I can't stand it.

384
00:45:16,277 --> 00:45:17,611
Mom didn't see the paper?

385
00:45:17,820 --> 00:45:20,532
I don't think so.
She'd never believe it...

386
00:45:22,159 --> 00:45:23,660
You're right.
You should go home.

387
00:45:23,869 --> 00:45:24,870
Bye.

388
00:45:30,501 --> 00:45:32,295
Call me, Michel.

389
00:45:32,795 --> 00:45:34,464
Please, call me.

390
00:45:37,342 --> 00:45:38,844
Did you see the picture?

391
00:45:39,052 --> 00:45:40,053
The picture?

392
00:45:41,555 --> 00:45:42,431
Is that you, Jacques?

393
00:45:42,639 --> 00:45:45,018
Isn't it amazing?
You didn't see it?

394
00:45:46,728 --> 00:45:48,229
I forgot.
I've had a hard day.

395
00:45:48,438 --> 00:45:50,523
Come meet us.
it'll relax you.

396
00:45:50,732 --> 00:45:51,399
Where?

397
00:45:57,031 --> 00:45:58,115
Not bad!

398
00:49:24,679 --> 00:49:26,848
I'm sorry to bother you...

399
00:49:27,056 --> 00:49:29,517
Someone played a stupid prank.
I can't get in.

400
00:49:32,938 --> 00:49:33,689
Those kids...

401
00:49:33,898 --> 00:49:35,983
Turks. Always trouble.

402
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:40,112
I don't know.
They stuck chewing gum in my lock.

403
00:49:40,654 --> 00:49:41,948
Tweezers.

404
00:49:52,835 --> 00:49:53,586
It's me.

405
00:49:53,794 --> 00:49:54,837
Michel...

406
00:49:55,046 --> 00:49:57,006
I just called.
There was no answer.

407
00:49:58,090 --> 00:50:01,136
Someone stuck chewing gum
in my lock.

408
00:50:01,345 --> 00:50:02,721
I heard the phone.

409
00:50:02,930 --> 00:50:03,764
Chewing gum?

410
00:50:06,058 --> 00:50:09,187
I did an ad for chewing gum.
That must be why.

411
00:50:10,104 --> 00:50:12,690
I told you not to.
They take advantage of you.

412
00:50:14,942 --> 00:50:16,195
Forget It.

413
00:50:17,029 --> 00:50:18,530
There was no answering machine.

414
00:50:22,868 --> 00:50:24,371
All I want is peace.

415
00:50:25,955 --> 00:50:27,540
A life of peace and quiet.

416
00:50:27,749 --> 00:50:30,210
Life won't be peaceful with me.

417
00:50:32,880 --> 00:50:34,632
Did you meet someone?

418
00:50:35,091 --> 00:50:37,510
No. I'm waiting for you.

419
00:50:37,968 --> 00:50:40,596
Why didn't you answer before?

420
00:50:40,806 --> 00:50:43,558
I told you.
I couldn't get inside.

421
00:50:43,767 --> 00:50:44,893
I understand.

422
00:50:47,896 --> 00:50:49,190
How are you?

423
00:50:49,398 --> 00:50:51,484
I'm going to Hungary next week.

424
00:50:52,860 --> 00:50:54,237
What are you doing?

425
00:50:54,654 --> 00:50:55,488
I'm going to bed.

426
00:50:55,696 --> 00:50:56,614
Go ahead

427
00:50:57,658 --> 00:50:58,826
Go on..

428
00:51:01,703 --> 00:51:02,913
Are you there?

429
00:51:04,540 --> 00:51:05,999
Michel, are you there?

430
00:51:11,589 --> 00:51:13,007
It's starting again...

431
00:51:37,118 --> 00:51:38,160
Are you asleep?

432
00:51:38,786 --> 00:51:39,954
No, I'm not.

433
00:51:40,205 --> 00:51:41,498
Get into bed.

434
00:51:43,625 --> 00:51:44,751
Are you in bed?

435
00:51:45,127 --> 00:51:47,295
I'm taking a shower.
I was getting undressed.

436
00:51:47,546 --> 00:51:49,048
No one is helping you?

437
00:51:53,636 --> 00:51:55,263
Valentine, are you there?

438
00:51:56,180 --> 00:51:57,266
No. Goodnight.

439
00:52:12,031 --> 00:52:14,076
I knew you'd make it.

440
00:52:15,578 --> 00:52:17,121
Did they ask the question?

441
00:52:17,454 --> 00:52:20,624
From the book
you dropped in the street.

442
00:52:52,952 --> 00:52:54,370
You don't Like it?

443
00:52:55,330 --> 00:52:56,498
Yes. Very much.

444
00:52:58,751 --> 00:53:01,170
What will be
the first judgment I sign?

445
00:53:29,326 --> 00:53:30,828
Civil hearing.

446
00:53:31,787 --> 00:53:34,207
The inhabitants of Pinchat

447
00:53:34,415 --> 00:53:37,084
against Joseph Kern.
Please enter.

448
00:54:40,614 --> 00:54:44,743
I'd like number 432.
Van den Budenmayer.

449
00:54:45,327 --> 00:54:47,121
- Did I pronounce it right?
- Yes.

450
00:54:49,040 --> 00:54:50,166
This one?

451
00:54:52,836 --> 00:54:54,671
just sold the last one.

452
00:54:56,840 --> 00:55:00,302
I'll have others this afternoon.
I can set one aside.

453
00:55:11,314 --> 00:55:12,900
Whose paper is this?

454
00:55:13,150 --> 00:55:14,318
Yours.

455
00:55:48,523 --> 00:55:49,315
I came...

456
00:55:51,025 --> 00:55:52,735
I saw the newspaper...

457
00:55:52,944 --> 00:55:55,030
I want you to know
I didn't tell a soul.

458
00:55:55,239 --> 00:55:56,615
I know.

459
00:55:57,450 --> 00:56:00,411
No one. Not the police. No one.

460
00:56:00,661 --> 00:56:01,871
I know.

461
00:56:05,375 --> 00:56:06,710
I know who it was.

462
00:56:08,378 --> 00:56:09,421
Who?

463
00:56:10,672 --> 00:56:12,008
It was me.

464
00:56:13,843 --> 00:56:15,720
You asked me to.

465
00:56:16,721 --> 00:56:18,180
Won't you come in?

466
00:56:19,850 --> 00:56:21,685
Let me show you something.

467
00:56:41,206 --> 00:56:45,128
One, two, three, four, five, six.

468
00:56:46,171 --> 00:56:46,838
Seven?

469
00:56:47,964 --> 00:56:49,007
Seven.

470
00:56:50,759 --> 00:56:53,429
Won't you have some pear brandy?

471
00:57:01,312 --> 00:57:04,483
I've had it for ages,
but I've never had an occasion.

472
00:57:20,834 --> 00:57:22,085
To my health.

473
00:57:28,426 --> 00:57:30,220
Why did you do it?

474
00:57:30,887 --> 00:57:32,847
Why did I turn myself in?

475
00:57:33,264 --> 00:57:34,182
Yes.

476
00:57:36,644 --> 00:57:39,939
To see what you'd do
once you saw it in your paper.

477
00:57:41,690 --> 00:57:42,441
You thought

478
00:57:42,650 --> 00:57:43,567
I would come?

479
00:57:43,776 --> 00:57:46,613
After our last conversation,
I thought so.

480
00:57:48,114 --> 00:57:49,532
Why?

481
00:57:58,000 --> 00:57:59,794
Do you expect something
from me?

482
00:58:00,002 --> 00:58:01,045
Yes.

483
00:58:04,007 --> 00:58:06,385
Before you left,
you mentioned

484
00:58:06,593 --> 00:58:07,636
pity.

485
00:58:09,137 --> 00:58:11,349
Afterwards, I realized
it was disgust.

486
00:58:23,904 --> 00:58:26,031
Will you sit down for a moment?

487
00:58:34,833 --> 00:58:36,001
Will you smile for me?

488
00:58:43,593 --> 00:58:45,637
The day you left,

489
00:58:45,846 --> 00:58:47,013
you cried.

490
00:58:47,472 --> 00:58:48,515
I cried.

491
00:58:52,186 --> 00:58:54,146
And I shut off my radio.

492
00:58:56,232 --> 00:58:58,192
I sat down at my desk.

493
00:58:59,193 --> 00:59:03,240
The fountain pen I'd used
all my life was out of ink,

494
00:59:03,448 --> 00:59:05,033
so I took a pencil

495
00:59:05,659 --> 00:59:08,704
and wrote letters to my neighbors
and to the police.

496
00:59:10,206 --> 00:59:11,874
I mailed them that evening.

497
00:59:12,542 --> 00:59:14,544
While you were sleeping soundly.

498
00:59:15,128 --> 00:59:16,796
I wasn't sleeping.

499
00:59:18,465 --> 00:59:19,258
I had gone bowling.

500
00:59:22,344 --> 00:59:25,180
Do you remember
that couple's conversation?

501
00:59:25,431 --> 00:59:27,016
The boy and the girl?

502
00:59:29,144 --> 00:59:30,437
I remember.

503
00:59:31,146 --> 00:59:32,564
They wanted to go too.

504
00:59:32,772 --> 00:59:34,274
That same evening.

505
00:59:35,234 --> 00:59:37,611
Maybe you were
right next to them.

506
00:59:40,489 --> 00:59:41,657
Maybe.

507
00:59:44,828 --> 00:59:46,413
You didn't like her.

508
00:59:49,458 --> 00:59:51,209
It's almost over.
I was right.

509
00:59:55,339 --> 00:59:57,508
You seem happy about it.

510
01:00:04,141 --> 01:00:06,143
Did you provoke it?

511
01:00:14,777 --> 01:00:15,987
Yes or no?

512
01:00:18,949 --> 01:00:22,119
Because of my eavesdropping
and my trial,

513
01:00:22,661 --> 01:00:23,829
the girl met

514
01:00:24,038 --> 01:00:25,457
another man.

515
01:00:57,283 --> 01:00:58,576
Good day.

516
01:01:02,206 --> 01:01:04,166
Since then, she's been alone.

517
01:01:05,083 --> 01:01:07,377
I asked my brother
to go see her.

518
01:01:08,004 --> 01:01:10,006
He stayed three days.

519
01:01:14,260 --> 01:01:17,139
in one week
I'm going to England.

520
01:01:17,431 --> 01:01:19,433
I'm abandoning my mother
and my brother.

521
01:01:19,683 --> 01:01:21,936
Every day he gets a little worse.

522
01:01:22,811 --> 01:01:24,355
I shouldn't leave.

523
01:01:24,564 --> 01:01:27,317
Leave. It's your destiny.

524
01:01:27,817 --> 01:01:29,694
You can't live your brother's life

525
01:01:29,903 --> 01:01:31,071
for him.

526
01:01:37,286 --> 01:01:38,537
I love him.

527
01:01:41,123 --> 01:01:42,834
If only I could help.

528
01:01:43,543 --> 01:01:44,670
You can.

529
01:01:45,170 --> 01:01:46,213
Be.

530
01:01:47,339 --> 01:01:48,882
What do you mean?

531
01:01:49,842 --> 01:01:52,345
That's all: be.

532
01:01:57,016 --> 01:01:59,311
Do you like flying?

533
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:01,146
Then take the ferry.

534
01:02:02,815 --> 01:02:04,608
I've never taken one.

535
01:02:04,858 --> 01:02:07,404
It's less expensive and healthier.

536
01:02:07,654 --> 01:02:09,072
That's a good idea.

537
01:02:18,707 --> 01:02:20,042
Do you like it?

538
01:02:21,418 --> 01:02:23,420
Today is my birthday.

539
01:02:23,755 --> 01:02:25,132
I didn't know.

540
01:02:28,218 --> 01:02:32,640
35 years ago today,
at about the same time, 5 o'clock,

541
01:02:33,641 --> 01:02:35,810
I acquitted a man. A sailor.

542
01:02:37,687 --> 01:02:41,858
One of my first big cases.
it was a tough time in my life.

543
01:02:44,194 --> 01:02:47,614
I have since realized
I made a mistake.

544
01:02:49,158 --> 01:02:50,910
He was guilty.

545
01:02:55,957 --> 01:02:57,835
I'm all out of bulbs.

546
01:03:26,992 --> 01:03:28,535
What happened to him?

547
01:03:29,661 --> 01:03:31,581
I did my own investigation.

548
01:03:32,290 --> 01:03:35,501
He's married with three children.

549
01:03:35,877 --> 01:03:38,045
A grandson.

550
01:03:39,380 --> 01:03:40,716
He is living in peace.

551
01:03:43,302 --> 01:03:45,679
So you did what was necessary.

552
01:03:49,559 --> 01:03:51,144
And you did it well.

553
01:03:57,318 --> 01:03:59,028
Don't you understand?

554
01:04:01,155 --> 01:04:02,531
You saved him.

555
01:04:03,991 --> 01:04:05,452
Perhaps.

556
01:04:06,369 --> 01:04:10,081
But how many others
could I have acquitted? Even guilty?

557
01:04:12,083 --> 01:04:16,589
Deciding what is true and what isn't
now seems to me

558
01:04:17,798 --> 01:04:19,842
a lack of modesty.

559
01:04:22,011 --> 01:04:23,055
Vanity?

560
01:04:24,890 --> 01:04:26,099
Vanity.

561
01:04:36,235 --> 01:04:37,862
Can I have a drop?

562
01:04:48,458 --> 01:04:49,626
To you!

563
01:04:54,172 --> 01:04:56,049
If I had to go to court...

564
01:04:57,551 --> 01:05:00,304
are there still judges like you?

565
01:05:01,514 --> 01:05:03,307
You won't go to court.

566
01:05:04,433 --> 01:05:06,937
Justice doesn't deal
with the innocent.

567
01:05:09,940 --> 01:05:11,358
See that?

568
01:05:11,816 --> 01:05:14,153
It's the sixth window
they've broken.

569
01:05:14,362 --> 01:05:18,532
The wavelength has been changed.
I can no longer eavesdrop.

570
01:05:20,868 --> 01:05:22,412
Where is the broom?

571
01:05:22,621 --> 01:05:24,581
In the kitchen closet.

572
01:05:46,522 --> 01:05:48,650
Put the stone
on the piano.

573
01:06:07,546 --> 01:06:08,922
You're not afraid?

574
01:06:11,675 --> 01:06:14,428
I wonder what I'd do
in their place.

575
01:06:16,472 --> 01:06:17,765
The same thing.

576
01:06:19,350 --> 01:06:21,145
You'd throw stones?

577
01:06:21,520 --> 01:06:24,356
in their place? Of course.

578
01:06:25,440 --> 01:06:27,860
And that goes
for everyone judged.

579
01:06:28,277 --> 01:06:31,030
Given their lives,
I would steal,

580
01:06:31,281 --> 01:06:34,117
I'd kill, I'd lie.
Of course I would.

581
01:06:37,830 --> 01:06:39,623
ALL that because I wasn't

582
01:06:39,832 --> 01:06:41,458
in their shoes, but mine.

583
01:06:47,173 --> 01:06:49,050
is there someone you love?

584
01:06:55,766 --> 01:06:57,560
Have you ever loved?

585
01:07:05,152 --> 01:07:06,611
Yesterday I dreamt...

586
01:07:09,740 --> 01:07:11,199
I dreamt of you.

587
01:07:14,912 --> 01:07:17,331
You were 40 or 50 years old,

588
01:07:19,417 --> 01:07:21,086
and you were happy.

589
01:07:23,172 --> 01:07:25,424
Do your dreams come true?

590
01:07:28,510 --> 01:07:31,556
It's been years
since I dreamt something nice.

591
01:08:20,319 --> 01:08:21,612
Stay there!

592
01:11:10,842 --> 01:11:12,635
I bought a ticket
for the ferry.

593
01:11:12,886 --> 01:11:16,306
I arrive in England
next Wednesday.

594
01:11:20,186 --> 01:11:21,979
At 7:30 a. m.

595
01:11:22,229 --> 01:11:23,606
Why the ferry?

596
01:11:24,899 --> 01:11:27,652
So I can visit my mother
near Calais.

597
01:11:28,570 --> 01:11:31,573
I'll meet you at 8:00.

598
01:11:32,657 --> 01:11:34,201
I'm happy you're coming.

599
01:11:35,953 --> 01:11:37,288
Michel, tell me...

600
01:11:38,706 --> 01:11:39,624
do you love me?

601
01:11:39,874 --> 01:11:41,042
I think so.

602
01:11:42,794 --> 01:11:44,379
You love me
or you think so?

603
01:11:44,588 --> 01:11:46,048
It's the same thing.

604
01:13:13,103 --> 01:13:14,521
The battery.

605
01:14:17,174 --> 01:14:18,676
Auguste!

606
01:14:53,673 --> 01:14:55,800
Personal weather reports.

607
01:14:56,009 --> 01:14:58,554
I've tried calling
for a few days.

608
01:14:58,763 --> 01:15:00,347
I was sick. I'm sorry.

609
01:15:00,556 --> 01:15:03,934
What will the weather be
on the English Channel next week?

610
01:15:04,143 --> 01:15:07,647
Wonderful. Sunny, a slight breeze,
chilly in the morning.

611
01:15:07,856 --> 01:15:09,232
Why are you laughing?

612
01:15:09,441 --> 01:15:12,402
I intend to go there.
Even farther.

613
01:15:12,611 --> 01:15:13,779
For your work?

614
01:15:13,987 --> 01:15:16,574
No, for pleasure. On a yacht.

615
01:15:16,782 --> 01:15:18,117
It's a nice sail.

616
01:15:18,326 --> 01:15:19,577
Yes, very.

617
01:15:19,785 --> 01:15:20,953
You'll be closing?

618
01:15:21,162 --> 01:15:22,580
I'll have to.

619
01:15:22,788 --> 01:15:25,250
That's too bad.
It was a good idea. Goodbye.

620
01:16:03,459 --> 01:16:05,879
We told you
not to smile!

621
01:16:07,005 --> 01:16:08,256
Be serious!

622
01:16:09,758 --> 01:16:13,011
Can you send an invitation
to this address?

623
01:16:13,261 --> 01:16:14,514
Just one person?

624
01:19:05,829 --> 01:19:06,997
Are you okay?

625
01:19:08,457 --> 01:19:09,583
- So long.
- Have a good time.

626
01:19:18,134 --> 01:19:19,552
There's no make-up remover?

627
01:19:19,761 --> 01:19:20,721
Here.

628
01:19:33,610 --> 01:19:34,611
Everyone noticed

629
01:19:34,819 --> 01:19:35,862
that guy.

630
01:19:36,613 --> 01:19:40,159
During the entire show
I kept staring at him.

631
01:20:05,354 --> 01:20:06,814
You came.

632
01:20:08,148 --> 01:20:10,150
You knew the invitation
came from me?

633
01:20:10,359 --> 01:20:11,611
I'd hoped so.

634
01:20:12,612 --> 01:20:14,197
Did you look for me?

635
01:20:15,031 --> 01:20:16,783
During the entire show.

636
01:20:20,287 --> 01:20:22,581
I'm leaving tomorrow.
I wanted to say goodbye.

637
01:20:23,958 --> 01:20:25,000
Goodbye.

638
01:20:27,921 --> 01:20:30,590
I'd like you
to tell me in detail

639
01:20:30,966 --> 01:20:32,592
the dream you had.

640
01:20:35,262 --> 01:20:37,139
You were 50 years old

641
01:20:37,974 --> 01:20:39,517
and you were happy.

642
01:20:41,018 --> 01:20:42,311
in this dream...

643
01:20:44,272 --> 01:20:46,233
was there someone else?

644
01:20:47,359 --> 01:20:48,485
There was.

645
01:20:50,404 --> 01:20:51,405
Who?

646
01:20:55,910 --> 01:20:57,537
You woke up

647
01:20:58,329 --> 01:21:00,748
and you smiled at someone
next to you.

648
01:21:01,749 --> 01:21:03,210
I don't know who.

649
01:21:04,920 --> 01:21:06,714
That's what will happen?

650
01:21:08,424 --> 01:21:09,967
in 20 or 25 years?

651
01:21:10,552 --> 01:21:11,469
Yes.

652
01:21:17,183 --> 01:21:19,145
What else do you know?

653
01:21:21,439 --> 01:21:22,022
Who are you?

654
01:21:23,858 --> 01:21:25,401
A retired judge.

655
01:21:27,612 --> 01:21:30,615
I feel something important
is happening around me.

656
01:21:32,367 --> 01:21:33,743
And it scares me.

657
01:21:45,299 --> 01:21:46,466
is that better?

658
01:21:50,345 --> 01:21:51,722
I used to come here often.

659
01:21:53,683 --> 01:21:55,351
Where did you usually sit?

660
01:21:56,728 --> 01:21:58,146
Where I sat today.

661
01:21:59,731 --> 01:22:01,901
That's why you couldn't see me.

662
01:22:07,865 --> 01:22:09,993
One day,
during the intermission,

663
01:22:10,785 --> 01:22:13,288
the elastic holding my books broke.

664
01:22:14,956 --> 01:22:15,540
One of them,

665
01:22:15,749 --> 01:22:18,794
a big one,
fell down...

666
01:22:19,587 --> 01:22:21,297
somewhere around here.

667
01:22:23,341 --> 01:22:27,054
it was just before my exams.
I ran down immediately.

668
01:22:27,596 --> 01:22:30,974
The book had opened to a certain
page. I read a few sentences.

669
01:22:31,683 --> 01:22:34,478
it was the question they asked
during my exam.

670
01:22:35,646 --> 01:22:38,107
Getting out of the house
did you good.

671
01:22:40,026 --> 01:22:41,652
I had to recharge the battery.

672
01:22:42,570 --> 01:22:43,739
it was dead.

673
01:22:46,575 --> 01:22:47,618
The storm.

674
01:23:17,568 --> 01:23:19,195
Lousy coffee.

675
01:23:21,572 --> 01:23:22,949
I was wondering

676
01:23:24,116 --> 01:23:25,743
why you mentioned that sailor.

677
01:23:26,870 --> 01:23:28,330
Do you know why?

678
01:23:31,792 --> 01:23:32,793
Yes.

679
01:23:41,094 --> 01:23:42,595
Because

680
01:23:44,807 --> 01:23:47,893
you didn't want to tell me
something more important.

681
01:23:52,107 --> 01:23:55,026
About the woman
that you loved.

682
01:23:59,364 --> 01:24:00,741
She betrayed you.

683
01:24:04,787 --> 01:24:06,580
She betrayed you,

684
01:24:07,915 --> 01:24:10,210
and you never understood why.

685
01:24:14,214 --> 01:24:16,007
And you kept on loving her.

686
01:24:18,761 --> 01:24:20,596
How do you know all this?

687
01:24:26,270 --> 01:24:28,397
it wasn't hard to guess.

688
01:24:31,149 --> 01:24:32,526
What was she Like?

689
01:24:34,779 --> 01:24:37,156
She graduated
two years before me.

690
01:24:41,703 --> 01:24:43,622
She was blond,

691
01:24:44,331 --> 01:24:45,916
delicate,

692
01:24:47,209 --> 01:24:50,296
radiant, with a long neck.

693
01:24:53,300 --> 01:24:56,845
Her clothing and her furniture
were all light-colored.

694
01:24:58,179 --> 01:25:01,934
In the foyer there was a mirror
in a white frame.

695
01:25:04,437 --> 01:25:06,063
it was in that mirror,

696
01:25:06,522 --> 01:25:08,108
one night,

697
01:25:09,109 --> 01:25:11,069
that I saw her white Legs spread,

698
01:25:13,864 --> 01:25:15,908
with a man between them.

699
01:25:20,621 --> 01:25:21,622
Why?

700
01:25:22,540 --> 01:25:24,376
did that happen?

701
01:25:25,127 --> 01:25:26,503
Do you know?

702
01:25:27,129 --> 01:25:31,258
This man,
whose name was Hugo Holbling,

703
01:25:35,346 --> 01:25:37,390
could offer her what she wanted.

704
01:25:39,893 --> 01:25:41,437
They left.

705
01:25:43,939 --> 01:25:45,649
I followed them.

706
01:25:47,318 --> 01:25:49,863
I crossed France, the Channel...

707
01:25:52,157 --> 01:25:53,533
I was...

708
01:25:54,326 --> 01:25:55,744
humiliated.

709
01:25:58,331 --> 01:26:01,125
Until the day she died
in an accident.

710
01:26:04,045 --> 01:26:06,923
Since then,
I've never loved another woman.

711
01:26:08,592 --> 01:26:09,259
Yes.

712
01:26:09,926 --> 01:26:11,720
I stopped believing.

713
01:26:13,972 --> 01:26:16,267
Maybe I never met the woman...

714
01:26:20,229 --> 01:26:23,399
Maybe you're the woman
I never met.

715
01:26:25,486 --> 01:26:27,321
The story doesn't end there.

716
01:26:27,780 --> 01:26:29,031
No.

717
01:26:30,741 --> 01:26:32,619
A while ago,

718
01:26:32,827 --> 01:26:35,080
I was given a difficult case.

719
01:26:35,580 --> 01:26:38,958
On it was written the name
of the defendant:

720
01:26:39,167 --> 01:26:40,711
Hugo Holbling.

721
01:26:40,920 --> 01:26:42,338
The same man.

722
01:26:43,297 --> 01:26:44,799
He'd come back here.

723
01:26:51,097 --> 01:26:52,474
I'm closing up.

724
01:26:54,935 --> 01:26:56,728
Did you see a woman
with a bucket?

725
01:27:01,192 --> 01:27:03,110
The storm flooded the wardrobe.

726
01:27:03,528 --> 01:27:04,278
If you see her,

727
01:27:04,820 --> 01:27:06,281
tell her I'm upstairs.

728
01:27:12,746 --> 01:27:14,832
You shouldn't have taken the case.

729
01:27:15,458 --> 01:27:16,668
I didn't want to.

730
01:27:22,006 --> 01:27:23,342
At first,
I wanted to kill him.

731
01:27:25,678 --> 01:27:28,764
I would have,
if it would have changed something.

732
01:27:31,768 --> 01:27:32,644
Now,

733
01:27:33,687 --> 01:27:35,563
he was waiting for my verdict.

734
01:27:38,274 --> 01:27:41,445
He was building
a covered market which caved in.

735
01:27:41,654 --> 01:27:43,614
Several people died.

736
01:27:46,242 --> 01:27:48,077
I said he was guilty.

737
01:27:49,621 --> 01:27:51,581
It was a legal sentence.

738
01:27:56,044 --> 01:27:59,006
Afterwards,
I asked for early retirement.

739
01:28:03,052 --> 01:28:04,470
Did you see her?

740
01:28:08,016 --> 01:28:09,434
I'm always running after her!

741
01:28:12,479 --> 01:28:13,647
Milana!

742
01:28:22,867 --> 01:28:26,495
There you are! Give me the buckets.
They're heavy.

743
01:28:34,838 --> 01:28:36,798
You seemed to Like
my pear brandy.

744
01:28:37,007 --> 01:28:39,677
I have another favor to ask you.

745
01:28:40,636 --> 01:28:42,596
I'll be gone two or three weeks.

746
01:28:43,347 --> 01:28:45,016
I'll come see you afterwards.

747
01:28:46,767 --> 01:28:49,396
Please give me
one of the puppies.

748
01:28:52,357 --> 01:28:54,526
Will the fashion show be on TV?

749
01:28:55,444 --> 01:28:56,738
Probably.

750
01:28:57,280 --> 01:28:59,490
I better buy a TV.

751
01:28:59,699 --> 01:29:01,826
I have one I never use.

752
01:29:02,326 --> 01:29:03,745
My brother
can bring it to you.

753
01:29:03,953 --> 01:29:04,997
His name is Marc.

754
01:29:05,205 --> 01:29:08,250
I'd Like to meet him.
I'll see you soon.

755
01:29:09,418 --> 01:29:10,753
Goodbye.

756
01:29:15,175 --> 01:29:17,135
Do you have your ticket?

757
01:30:44,857 --> 01:30:46,401
Where do I go?

758
01:30:46,610 --> 01:30:48,487
This deck. That corridor.

759
01:30:56,037 --> 01:30:58,081
Excuse me, I'm lost. F38?

760
01:30:58,331 --> 01:30:59,082
The deck above.

761
